  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Commission to Joshua"
      title: "God\u2019s Commission to Joshua"
      number: 1
      content: "After the death of Moses the servant of the Lord, it came to pass
        that the Lord spoke to Joshua the son of Nun, Moses\u2019 assistant, saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CMoses My servant is dead. Now therefore, arise, go over this
        Jordan, you and all this people, to the land which I am giving to them\u2014the
        children of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every place that the sole of your foot will tread upon I have given
        you, as I said to Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From the wilderness and this Lebanon as far as the great river, the
        River Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites, and to the Great Sea toward
        the going down of the sun, shall be your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No man shall be  able  to stand before you all the days of your life;
        as I was with Moses, so  I will be with you. I will not leave you nor forsake
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Be strong and of good courage, for to this people you shall divide
        as an inheritance the land which I swore to their fathers to give them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Only be strong and very courageous, that you may observe to do according
        to all the law which Moses My servant commanded you; do not turn from it
        to the right hand or to the left, that you may prosper wherever you go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth, but you shall
        meditate in it day and night, that you may observe to do according to all
        that is written in it. For then you will make your way prosperous, and then
        you will have good success. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Order to Cross the Jordan'
      title: The Order to Cross the Jordan
      number: 9
      content: "Have I not commanded you? Be strong and of good courage; do not be
        afraid, nor be dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CPass through the camp and command the people, saying, \u2018Prepare
        provisions for yourselves, for within three days you will cross over this
        Jordan, to go in to possess the land which the Lord your God is giving you
        to possess.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh
        Joshua spoke, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CRemember the word which Moses the servant of the Lord commanded
        you, saying, \u2018The Lord your God is giving you rest and is giving you
        this land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your wives, your little ones, and your livestock shall remain in
        the land which Moses gave you on this side of the Jordan. But you shall pass
        before your brethren armed, all your mighty men of valor, and help them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "until the Lord has given your brethren rest, as He gave you, and
        they also have taken possession of the land which the Lord your God is giving
        them. Then you shall return to the land of your possession and enjoy it,
        which Moses the Lord\u2019s servant gave you on this side of the Jordan toward
        the sunrise.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they answered Joshua, saying, \u201CAll that you command us we
        will do, and wherever you send us we will go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Just as we heeded Moses in all things, so we will heed you. Only
        the Lord your God be with you, as He was with Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Whoever rebels against your command and does not heed your words,
        in all that you command him, shall be put to death. Only be strong and of
        good courage.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rahab Hides the Spies'
      title: Rahab Hides the Spies
      number: 1
      content: "Now Joshua the son of Nun sent out two men from Acacia Grove to spy
        secretly, saying, \u201CGo, view the land, especially Jericho.\u201D So they
        went, and came to the house of a harlot named Rahab, and lodged there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was told the king of Jericho, saying, \u201CBehold, men have
        come here tonight from the children of Israel to search out the country.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So the king of Jericho sent to Rahab, saying, \u201CBring out the
        men who have come to you, who have entered your house, for they have come
        to search out all the country.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the woman took the two men and hid them. So she said, \u201CYes,
        the men came to me, but I did not know where they were from. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And it happened as the gate was being shut, when it was dark, that
        the men went out. Where the men went I do not know; pursue them quickly,
        for you may overtake them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(But she had brought them up to the roof and hidden them with the
        stalks of flax, which she had laid in order on the roof.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then the men pursued them by the road to the Jordan, to the fords.
        And as soon as those who pursued them had gone out, they shut the gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now before they lay down, she came up to them on the roof, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to the men: \u201CI know that the Lord has given you the
        land, that the terror of you has fallen on us, and that all the inhabitants
        of the land are fainthearted because of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For we have heard how the Lord  dried up the water of the Red Sea
        for you when you came out of Egypt, and what you did to the two kings of
        the Amorites who were on the other side of the Jordan, Sihon and Og, whom
        you utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And as soon as we heard these  things,  our hearts melted; neither
        did there remain any more courage in anyone because of you, for the Lord
        your God, He is God in heaven above and on earth beneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now therefore, I beg you, swear to me by the Lord, since I have shown
        you kindness, that you also will show kindness to my father\u2019s house,
        and give me a true token, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and spare my father, my mother, my brothers, my sisters, and all
        that they have, and deliver our lives from death.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the men answered her, \u201COur lives for yours, if none of you
        tell this business of ours. And it shall be, when the Lord has given us the
        land, that we will deal kindly and truly with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then she let them down by a rope through the window, for her house
        was on the city wall; she dwelt on the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And she said to them, \u201CGet to the mountain, lest the pursuers
        meet you. Hide there three days, until the pursuers have returned. Afterward
        you may go your way.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the men said to her: \u201CWe will  be  blameless of this oath
        of yours which you have made us swear, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "unless, when we come into the land, you bind this line of scarlet
        cord in the window through which you let us down, and unless you bring your
        father, your mother, your brothers, and all your father\u2019s household
        to your own home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So it shall be that whoever goes outside the doors of your house
        into the street, his blood shall  be on his own head, and we will  be guiltless.
        And whoever is with you in the house, his blood shall  be on our head if
        a hand is laid on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And if you tell this business of ours, then we will be free from
        your oath which you made us swear.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then she said, \u201CAccording to your words, so be it.\u201D And
        she sent them away, and they departed. And she bound the scarlet cord in
        the window."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They departed and went to the mountain, and stayed there three days
        until the pursuers returned. The pursuers sought them all along the way,
        but did not find them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the two men returned, descended from the mountain, and crossed
        over; and they came to Joshua the son of Nun, and told him all that had befallen
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they said to Joshua, \u201CTruly the Lord has delivered all the
        land into our hands, for indeed all the inhabitants of the country are fainthearted
        because of us.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Crosses the Jordan'
      title: Israel Crosses the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Joshua rose early in the morning; and they set out from Acacia
        Grove and came to the Jordan, he and all the children of Israel, and lodged
        there before they crossed over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So it was, after three days, that the officers went through the camp; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and they commanded the people, saying, \u201CWhen you see the ark
        of the covenant of the Lord your God, and the priests, the Levites, bearing
        it, then you shall set out from your place and go after it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet there shall be a space between you and it, about two thousand
        cubits by measure. Do not come near it, that you may know the way by which
        you must go, for you have not passed this way before.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Joshua said to the people, \u201CSanctify yourselves, for tomorrow
        the Lord will do wonders among you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Joshua spoke to the priests, saying, \u201CTake up the ark of
        the covenant and cross over before the people.\u201DSo they took up the ark
        of the covenant and went before the people."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CThis day I will begin to exalt
        you in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that, as I was with Moses,
        so I will be with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall command the priests who bear the ark of the covenant, saying,
        \u2018When you have come to the edge of the water of the Jordan, you shall
        stand in the Jordan.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Joshua said to the children of Israel, \u201CCome here, and hear
        the words of the Lord your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CBy this you shall know that the living God
        is among you, and that He will without fail drive out from before you the
        Canaanites and the Hittites and the Hivites and the Perizzites and the Girgashites
        and the Amorites and the Jebusites: "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth is crossing
        over before you into the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now therefore, take for yourselves twelve men from the tribes of
        Israel, one man from every tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it shall come to pass, as soon as the soles of the feet of the
        priests who bear the ark of the Lord, the Lord of all the earth, shall rest
        in the waters of the Jordan, that the waters of the Jordan shall be cut off,
        the waters that come down from upstream, and they shall stand as a heap.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So it was, when the people set out from their camp to cross over
        the Jordan, with the priests bearing the ark of the covenant before the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and as those who bore the ark came to the Jordan, and the feet of
        the priests who bore the ark dipped in the edge of the water (for the Jordan
        overflows all its banks during the whole time of harvest), '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'that the waters which came down from upstream stood still, and rose
        in a heap very far away at Adam, the city that is beside Zaretan. So the
        waters that went down into the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, failed, and
        were cut off; and the people crossed over opposite Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then the priests who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord stood
        firm on dry ground in the midst of the Jordan; and all Israel crossed over
        on dry ground, until all the people had crossed completely over the Jordan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Memorial Stones'
      title: The Memorial Stones
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass, when all the people had completely crossed over
        the Jordan, that the Lord spoke to Joshua, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake for yourselves twelve men from the people, one man from
        every tribe, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and command them, saying, \u2018Take for yourselves twelve stones
        from here, out of the midst of the Jordan, from the place where the priests\u2019
        feet stood firm. You shall carry them over with you and leave them in the
        lodging place where you lodge tonight.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Joshua called the twelve men whom he had appointed from the
        children of Israel, one man from every tribe; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and Joshua said to them: \u201CCross over before the ark of the Lord
        your God into the midst of the Jordan, and each one of you take up a stone
        on his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the children of
        Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "that this may be a sign among you when your children ask in time
        to come, saying, \u2018What do these stones mean to you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then you shall answer them that the waters of the Jordan were cut
        off before the ark of the covenant of the Lord; when it crossed over the
        Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. And these stones shall be
        for a memorial to the children of Israel forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the children of Israel did so, just as Joshua commanded, and
        took up twelve stones from the midst of the Jordan, as the Lord had spoken
        to Joshua, according to the number of the tribes of the children of Israel,
        and carried them over with them to the place where they lodged, and laid
        them down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then Joshua set up twelve stones in the midst of the Jordan, in the
        place where the feet of the priests who bore the ark of the covenant stood;
        and they are there to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the priests who bore the ark stood in the midst of the Jordan
        until everything was finished that the Lord had commanded Joshua to speak
        to the people, according to all that Moses had commanded Joshua; and the
        people hurried and crossed over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then it came to pass, when all the people had completely crossed
        over, that the ark of the Lord and the priests crossed over in the presence
        of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the men of Reuben, the men of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh
        crossed over armed before the children of Israel, as Moses had spoken to
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'About forty thousand prepared for war crossed over before the Lord
        for battle, to the plains of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: On that day the Lord  exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel; and
        they feared him, as they had feared Moses, all the days of his life.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Joshua, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CCommand the priests who bear the ark of the Testimony to come
        up from the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Joshua therefore commanded the priests, saying, \u201CCome up from
        the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And it came to pass, when the priests who bore the ark of the covenant
        of the Lord had come from the midst of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests\u2019
        feet touched the dry land, that the waters of the Jordan returned to their
        place and overflowed all its banks as before."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the people came up from the Jordan on the tenth day of the first
        month, and they camped in Gilgal on the east border of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And those twelve stones which they took out of the Jordan, Joshua
        set up in Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he spoke to the children of Israel, saying: \u201CWhen your
        children ask their fathers in time to come, saying, \u2018What are these
        stones?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "then you shall let your children know, saying, \u2018Israel crossed
        over this Jordan on dry land\u2019; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'for the Lord your God dried up the waters of the Jordan before you
        until you had crossed over, as the Lord your God did to the Red Sea, which
        He dried up before us until we had crossed over, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "that all the peoples of the earth may know the hand of the Lord,
        that it is  mighty, that you may fear the Lord your God forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Second Generation Circumcised'
      title: The Second Generation Circumcised
      number: 1
      content: So it was, when all the kings of the Amorites who were on the west
        side of the Jordan, and all the kings of the Canaanites who were by the sea,
        heard that the Lord had dried up the waters of the Jordan from before the
        children of Israel until we had crossed over, that their heart melted; and
        there was no spirit in them any longer because of the children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "At that time the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CMake flint knives for
        yourself, and circumcise the sons of Israel again the second time.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua made flint knives for himself, and circumcised the sons
        of Israel at the hill of the foreskins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And this is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: All the people
        who came out of Egypt who  were males, all the men of war, had died in the
        wilderness on the way, after they had come out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For all the people who came out had been circumcised, but all the
        people born in the wilderness, on the way as they came out of Egypt, had
        not been circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the children of Israel walked forty years in the wilderness,
        till all the people who  were men of war, who came out of Egypt, were consumed,
        because they did not obey the voice of the Lord\u2014to whom the Lord swore
        that He would not show them the land which the Lord had sworn to their fathers
        that He would give us, \u201Ca land flowing with milk and honey.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then Joshua circumcised their sons whom He raised up in their place;
        for they were uncircumcised, because they had not been circumcised on the
        way.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So it was, when they had finished circumcising all the people, that
        they stayed in their places in the camp till they were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CThis day I have rolled away the
        reproach of Egypt from you.\u201D Therefore the name of the place is called
        Gilgal to this day."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the children of Israel camped in Gilgal, and kept the Passover
        on the fourteenth day of the month at twilight on the plains of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they ate of the produce of the land on the day after the Passover,
        unleavened bread and parched grain, on the very same day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Commander of the Army of the Lord'
      title: The Commander of the Army of the Lord
      number: 12
      content: Then the manna ceased on the day after they had eaten the produce
        of the land; and the children of Israel no longer had manna, but they ate
        the food of the land of Canaan that year.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it came to pass, when Joshua was by Jericho, that he lifted his
        eyes and looked, and behold, a Man stood opposite him with His sword drawn
        in His hand. And Joshua went to Him and said to Him, \u201CAre You for us
        or for our adversaries?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So He said, \u201CNo, but as Commander of the army of the Lord I
        have now come.\u201DAnd Joshua fell on his face to the earth and worshiped,
        and said to Him, \u201CWhat does my Lord say to His servant?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Commander of the Lord\u2019s army said to Joshua, \u201CTake
        your sandal off your foot, for the place where you stand is holy.\u201D And
        Joshua did so."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Destruction of Jericho'
      title: The Destruction of Jericho
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Jericho was securely shut up because of the children of Israel;
        none went out, and none came in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to Joshua: \u201CSee! I have given Jericho into
        your hand, its king, and the mighty men of valor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall march around the city, all you men of war; you shall go
        all around the city once. This you shall do six days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And seven priests shall bear seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before
        the ark. But the seventh day you shall march around the city seven times,
        and the priests shall blow the trumpets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It shall come to pass, when they make a long blast with the ram\u2019s
        horn, and when you hear the sound of the trumpet, that all the people shall
        shout with a great shout; then the wall of the city will fall down flat.
        And the people shall go up every man straight before him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Joshua the son of Nun called the priests and said to them, \u201CTake
        up the ark of the covenant, and let seven priests bear seven trumpets of
        rams\u2019 horns before the ark of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to the people, \u201CProceed, and march around the city,
        and let him who is armed advance before the ark of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So it was, when Joshua had spoken to the people, that the seven priests
        bearing the seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before the Lord advanced and
        blew the trumpets, and the ark of the covenant of the Lord followed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The armed men went before the priests who blew the trumpets, and
        the rear guard came after the ark, while the  priests continued blowing the
        trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now Joshua had commanded the people, saying, \u201CYou shall not
        shout or make any noise with your voice, nor shall a word proceed out of
        your mouth, until the day I say to you, \u2018Shout!\u2019 Then you shall
        shout.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So he had the ark of the Lord circle the city, going around it once.
        Then they came into the camp and lodged in the camp.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Joshua rose early in the morning, and the priests took up the
        ark of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then seven priests bearing seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before
        the ark of the Lord went on continually and blew with the trumpets. And the
        armed men went before them. But the rear guard came after the ark of the
        Lord, while the  priests continued blowing the trumpets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And the second day they marched around the city once and returned
        to the camp. So they did six days.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But it came to pass on the seventh day that they rose early, about
        the dawning of the day, and marched around the city seven times in the same
        manner. On that day only they marched around the city seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the seventh time it happened, when the priests blew the trumpets,
        that Joshua said to the people: \u201CShout, for the Lord has given you the
        city! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the city shall be doomed by the Lord to destruction, it and all
        who are in it. Only Rahab the harlot shall live, she and all who are with
        her in the house, because she hid the messengers that we sent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you, by all means abstain from the accursed things, lest you
        become accursed when you take of the accursed things, and make the camp of
        Israel a curse, and trouble it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But all the silver and gold, and vessels of bronze and iron, are
        consecrated to the Lord; they shall come into the treasury of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the people shouted when the  priests blew the trumpets. And it
        happened when the people heard the sound of the trumpet, and the people shouted
        with a great shout, that the wall fell down flat. Then the people went up
        into the city, every man straight before him, and they took the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And they utterly destroyed all that was in the city, both man and
        woman, young and old, ox and sheep and donkey, with the edge of the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Joshua had said to the two men who had spied out the country,
        \u201CGo into the harlot\u2019s house, and from there bring out the woman
        and all that she has, as you swore to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the young men who had been spies went in and brought out Rahab,
        her father, her mother, her brothers, and all that she had. So they brought
        out all her relatives and left them outside the camp of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But they burned the city and all that was in it with fire. Only the
        silver and gold, and the vessels of bronze and iron, they put into the treasury
        of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joshua spared Rahab the harlot, her father\u2019s household,
        and all that she had. So she dwells in Israel to this day, because she hid
        the messengers whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Joshua charged them at that time, saying, \u201CCursed be the
        man before the Lord who rises up and builds this city Jericho; he shall lay
        its foundation with his firstborn, and with his youngest he shall set up
        its gates.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: So the Lord was with Joshua, and his fame spread throughout all the
        country.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Defeat at Ai'
      title: Defeat at Ai
      number: 1
      content: But the children of Israel committed a trespass regarding the accursed
        things, for Achan the son of Carmi, the son of Zabdi, the son of Zerah, of
        the tribe of Judah, took of the accursed things; so the anger of the Lord
        burned against the children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is beside Beth Aven,
        on the east side of Bethel, and spoke to them, saying, \u201CGo up and spy
        out the country.\u201D So the men went up and spied out Ai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they returned to Joshua and said to him, \u201CDo not let all
        the people go up, but let about two or three thousand men go up and attack
        Ai. Do not weary all the people there, for the  people  of  Ai  are few.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So about three thousand men went up there from the people, but they
        fled before the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And the men of Ai struck down about thirty-six men, for they chased
        them from before the gate as far as Shebarim, and struck them down on the
        descent; therefore the hearts of the people melted and became like water.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Joshua tore his clothes, and fell to the earth on his face before
        the ark of the Lord until evening, he and the elders of Israel; and they
        put dust on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CAlas, Lord God, why have You brought this
        people over the Jordan at all\u2014to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites,
        to destroy us? Oh, that we had been content, and dwelt on the other side
        of the Jordan! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord, what shall I say when Israel turns its back before its enemies? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Sin of Achan'
      title: The Sin of Achan
      number: 9
      content: "For the Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear
        it, and surround us, and cut off our name from the earth. Then what will
        You do for Your great name?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the Lord said to Joshua: \u201CGet up! Why do you lie thus on
        your face? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Israel has sinned, and they have also transgressed My covenant which
        I commanded them. For they have even taken some of the accursed things, and
        have both stolen and deceived; and they have also put it among their own
        stuff. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore the children of Israel could not stand before their enemies,
        but turned their backs before their enemies, because they have become doomed
        to destruction. Neither will I be with you anymore, unless you destroy the
        accursed from among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Get up, sanctify the people, and say, \u2018Sanctify yourselves for
        tomorrow, because thus says the Lord God of Israel: \u201CThere  is an accursed
        thing in your midst, O Israel; you cannot stand before your enemies until
        you take away the accursed thing from among you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning therefore you shall be brought according to your tribes.
        And it shall be that the tribe which the Lord takes shall come according
        to families; and the family which the Lord takes shall come by households;
        and the household which the Lord takes shall come man by man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then it shall be that he who is taken with the accursed thing shall
        be burned with fire, he and all that he has, because he has transgressed
        the covenant of the Lord, and because he has done a disgraceful thing in
        Israel.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua rose early in the morning and brought Israel by their tribes,
        and the tribe of Judah was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He brought the clan of Judah, and he took the family of the Zarhites;
        and he brought the family of the Zarhites man by man, and Zabdi was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then he brought his household man by man, and Achan the son of Carmi,
        the son of Zabdi, the son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was taken.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now Joshua said to Achan, \u201CMy son, I beg you, give glory to
        the Lord God of Israel, and make confession to Him, and tell me now what
        you have done; do not hide it from me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Achan answered Joshua and said, \u201CIndeed I have sinned against
        the Lord God of Israel, and this is what I have done: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When I saw among the spoils a beautiful Babylonian garment, two hundred
        shekels of silver, and a wedge of gold weighing fifty shekels, I coveted
        them and took them. And there they are, hidden in the earth in the midst
        of my tent, with the silver under it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and there it
        was, hidden in his tent, with the silver under it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they took them from the midst of the tent, brought them to Joshua
        and to all the children of Israel, and laid them out before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Joshua, and all Israel with him, took Achan the son of Zerah,
        the silver, the garment, the wedge of gold, his sons, his daughters, his
        oxen, his donkeys, his sheep, his tent, and all that he had, and they brought
        them to the Valley of Achor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CWhy have you troubled us? The Lord will trouble
        you this day.\u201D So all Israel stoned him with stones; and they burned
        them with fire after they had stoned them with stones."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Then they raised over him a great heap of stones, still there to this
        day. So the Lord turned from the fierceness of His anger. Therefore the name
        of that place has been called the Valley of Achor to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Ai'
      title: The Fall of Ai
      number: 1
      content: "Now the Lord said to Joshua: \u201CDo not be afraid, nor be dismayed;
        take all the people of war with you, and arise, go up to Ai. See, I have
        given into your hand the king of Ai, his people, his city, and his land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And you shall do to Ai and its king as you did to Jericho and its
        king. Only its spoil and its cattle you shall take as booty for yourselves.
        Lay an ambush for the city behind it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua arose, and all the people of war, to go up against Ai;
        and Joshua chose thirty thousand mighty men of valor and sent them away by
        night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he commanded them, saying: \u201CBehold, you shall lie in ambush
        against the city, behind the city. Do not go very far from the city, but
        all of you be ready. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I and all the people who are with me will approach the city;
        and it will come about, when they come out against us as at the first, that
        we shall flee before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For they will come out after us till we have drawn them from the
        city, for they will say, \u2018They  are fleeing before us as at the first.\u2019
        Therefore we will flee before them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then you shall rise from the ambush and seize the city, for the Lord
        your God will deliver it into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it will be, when you have taken the city, that you shall set
        the city on fire. According to the commandment of the Lord you shall do.
        See, I have commanded you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Joshua therefore sent them out; and they went to lie in ambush, and
        stayed between Bethel and Ai, on the west side of Ai; but Joshua lodged that
        night among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Joshua rose up early in the morning and mustered the people,
        and went up, he and the elders of Israel, before the people to Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And all the people of war who were with him went up and drew near;
        and they came before the city and camped on the north side of Ai. Now a valley
        lay between them and Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So he took about five thousand men and set them in ambush between
        Bethel and Ai, on the west side of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And when they had set the people, all the army that was on the north
        of the city, and its rear guard on the west of the city, Joshua went that
        night into the midst of the valley.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now it happened, when the king of Ai saw it, that the men of the
        city hurried and rose early and went out against Israel to battle, he and
        all his people, at an appointed place before the plain. But he did not know
        that there  was an ambush against him behind the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joshua and all Israel made as if they were beaten before them,
        and fled by the way of the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So all the people who were in Ai were called together to pursue them.
        And they pursued Joshua and were drawn away from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: There was not a man left in Ai or Bethel who did not go out after
        Israel. So they left the city open and pursued Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CStretch out the spear that is
        in your hand toward Ai, for I will give it into your hand.\u201D And Joshua
        stretched out the spear that was in his hand toward the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So those  in ambush arose quickly out of their place; they ran as
        soon as he had stretched out his hand, and they entered the city and took
        it, and hurried to set the city on fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And when the men of Ai looked behind them, they saw, and behold, the
        smoke of the city ascended to heaven. So they had no power to flee this way
        or that way, and the people who had fled to the wilderness turned back on
        the pursuers.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now when Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had taken the
        city and that the smoke of the city ascended, they turned back and struck
        down the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the others came out of the city against them; so they were caught
        in the midst of Israel, some on this side and some on that side. And they
        struck them down, so that they let none of them remain or escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But the king of Ai they took alive, and brought him to Joshua.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And it came to pass when Israel had made an end of slaying all the
        inhabitants of Ai in the field, in the wilderness where they pursued them,
        and when they all had fallen by the edge of the sword until they were consumed,
        that all the Israelites returned to Ai and struck it with the edge of the
        sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So it was that all who fell that day, both men and women, were twelve
        thousand\u2014all the people of Ai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For Joshua did not draw back his hand, with which he stretched out
        the spear, until he had utterly destroyed all the inhabitants of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Only the livestock and the spoil of that city Israel took as booty
        for themselves, according to the word of the Lord which He had commanded
        Joshua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joshua burned Ai and made it a heap forever, a desolation to this
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Joshua Renews the Covenant'
      title: Joshua Renews the Covenant
      number: 29
      content: And the king of Ai he hanged on a tree until evening. And as soon
        as the sun was down, Joshua commanded that they should take his corpse down
        from the tree, cast it at the entrance of the gate of the city, and raise
        over it a great heap of stones that  remains to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Joshua built an altar to the Lord God of Israel in Mount Ebal, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded the children of Israel,
        as it is written in the Book of the Law of Moses: \u201Can altar of whole
        stones over which no man has wielded an iron tool.\u201D And they offered
        on it burnt offerings to the Lord, and sacrificed peace offerings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And there, in the presence of the children of Israel, he wrote on
        the stones a copy of the law of Moses, which he had written. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then all Israel, with their elders and officers and judges, stood
        on either side of the ark before the priests, the Levites, who bore the ark
        of the covenant of the Lord, the stranger as well as he who was born among
        them. Half of them were in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them in front
        of Mount Ebal, as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded before, that
        they should bless the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And afterward he read all the words of the law, the blessings and
        the cursings, according to all that is written in the Book of the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: There was not a word of all that Moses had commanded which Joshua
        did not read before all the assembly of Israel, with the women, the little
        ones, and the strangers who were living among them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Treaty with the Gibeonites'
      title: The Treaty with the Gibeonites
      number: 1
      content: "And it came to pass when all the kings who were on this side of the
        Jordan, in the hills and in the lowland and in all the coasts of the Great
        Sea toward Lebanon\u2014the Hittite, the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite,
        the Hivite, and the Jebusite\u2014heard about  it,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: that they gathered together to fight with Joshua and Israel with one
        accord.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But when the inhabitants of Gibeon heard what Joshua had done to
        Jericho and Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'they worked craftily, and went and pretended to be ambassadors. And
        they took old sacks on their donkeys, old wineskins torn and mended, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'old and patched sandals on their feet, and old garments on themselves;
        and all the bread of their provision was dry and moldy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they went to Joshua, to the camp at Gilgal, and said to him and
        to the men of Israel, \u201CWe have come from a far country; now therefore,
        make a covenant with us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the men of Israel said to the Hivites, \u201CPerhaps you dwell
        among us; so how can we make a covenant with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they said to Joshua, \u201CWe are your servants.\u201DAnd Joshua
        said to them, \u201CWho are you, and where do you come from?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So they said to him: \u201CFrom a very far country your servants
        have come, because of the name of the Lord your God; for we have heard of
        His fame, and all that He did in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and all that He did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond
        the Jordan\u2014to Sihon king of Heshbon, and Og king of Bashan, who was
        at Ashtaroth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore our elders and all the inhabitants of our country spoke
        to us, saying, \u2018Take provisions with you for the journey, and go to
        meet them, and say to them, \u201CWe are your servants; now therefore, make
        a covenant with us.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'This bread of ours we took hot for our provision from our houses
        on the day we departed to come to you. But now look, it is dry and moldy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And these wineskins which we filled were new, and see, they are torn;
        and these our garments and our sandals have become old because of the very
        long journey.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the men of Israel took some of their provisions; but they did
        not ask counsel of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So Joshua made peace with them, and made a covenant with them to let
        them live; and the rulers of the congregation swore to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And it happened at the end of three days, after they had made a covenant
        with them, that they heard that they were their neighbors who dwelt near
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the children of Israel journeyed and came to their cities on
        the third day. Now their cities were  Gibeon, Chephirah, Beeroth, and Kirjath
        Jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But the children of Israel did not attack them, because the rulers
        of the congregation had sworn to them by the Lord God of Israel. And all
        the congregation complained against the rulers.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then all the rulers said to all the congregation, \u201CWe have sworn
        to them by the Lord God of Israel; now therefore, we may not touch them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This we will do to them: We will let them live, lest wrath be upon
        us because of the oath which we swore to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the rulers said to them, \u201CLet them live, but let them be
        woodcutters and water carriers for all the congregation, as the rulers had
        promised them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joshua called for them, and he spoke to them, saying, \u201CWhy
        have you deceived us, saying, \u2018We are very far from you,\u2019 when
        you dwell near us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore, you are  cursed, and none of you shall be freed from
        being slaves\u2014woodcutters and water carriers for the house of my God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they answered Joshua and said, \u201CBecause your servants were
        clearly told that the Lord your God commanded His servant Moses to give you
        all the land, and to destroy all the inhabitants of the land from before
        you; therefore we were very much afraid for our lives because of you, and
        have done this thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And now, here we are, in your hands; do with us as it seems good
        and right to do to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So he did to them, and delivered them out of the hand of the children
        of Israel, so that they did not kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And that day Joshua made them woodcutters and water carriers for the
        congregation and for the altar of the Lord, in the place which He would choose,
        even to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sun Stands Still'
      title: The Sun Stands Still
      number: 1
      content: "Now it came to pass when Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem heard how
        Joshua had taken Ai and had utterly destroyed it\u2014as he had done to Jericho
        and its king, so he had done to Ai and its king\u2014and how the inhabitants
        of Gibeon had made peace with Israel and were among them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that they feared greatly, because Gibeon was a great city, like one
        of the royal cities, and because it was greater than Ai, and all its men
        were mighty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem sent to Hoham king of Hebron,
        Piram king of Jarmuth, Japhia king of Lachish, and Debir king of Eglon, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CCome up to me and help me, that we may attack Gibeon, for it
        has made peace with Joshua and with the children of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Therefore the five kings of the Amorites, the king of Jerusalem, the
        king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of
        Eglon, gathered together and went up, they and all their armies, and camped
        before Gibeon and made war against it.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the men of Gibeon sent to Joshua at the camp at Gilgal, saying,
        \u201CDo not forsake your servants; come up to us quickly, save us and help
        us, for all the kings of the Amorites who dwell in the mountains have gathered
        together against us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua ascended from Gilgal, he and all the people of war with
        him, and all the mighty men of valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CDo not fear them, for I have delivered
        them into your hand; not a man of them shall stand before you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Joshua therefore came upon them suddenly, having marched all night
        from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Lord  routed them before Israel, killed them with a great
        slaughter at Gibeon, chased them along the road that goes to Beth Horon,
        and struck them down as far as Azekah and Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And it happened, as they fled before Israel and were on the descent
        of Beth Horon, that the Lord cast down large hailstones from heaven on them
        as far as Azekah, and they died. There  were more who died from the hailstones
        than the children of Israel killed with the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joshua spoke to the Lord in the day when the Lord delivered
        up the Amorites before the children of Israel, and he said in the sight of
        Israel:\u201CSun, stand still over Gibeon;And Moon, in the Valley of Aijalon.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the sun stood still,And the moon stopped,Till the people had revengeUpon
        their enemies.Is this not written in the Book of Jasher? So the sun stood
        still in the midst of heaven, and did not hasten to go down for about a whole
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And there has been no day like that, before it or after it, that the
        Lord heeded the voice of a man; for the Lord fought for Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Amorite Kings Executed'
      title: The Amorite Kings Executed
      number: 15
      content: Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But these five kings had fled and hidden themselves in a cave at
        Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And it was told Joshua, saying, \u201CThe five kings have been found
        hidden in the cave at Makkedah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Joshua said, \u201CRoll large stones against the mouth of the
        cave, and set men by it to guard them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And do not stay there yourselves, but pursue your enemies, and attack
        their rear guard. Do not allow them to enter their cities, for the Lord your
        God has delivered them into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then it happened, while Joshua and the children of Israel made an
        end of slaying them with a very great slaughter, till they had finished,
        that those who escaped entered fortified cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And all the people returned to the camp, to Joshua at Makkedah, in
        peace.No one moved his tongue against any of the children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joshua said, \u201COpen the mouth of the cave, and bring out
        those five kings to me from the cave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they did so, and brought out those five kings to him from the
        cave: the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the
        king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon.'
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So it was, when they brought out those kings to Joshua, that Joshua
        called for all the men of Israel, and said to the captains of the men of
        war who went with him, \u201CCome near, put your feet on the necks of these
        kings.\u201D And they drew near and put their feet on their necks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joshua said to them, \u201CDo not be afraid, nor be dismayed;
        be strong and of good courage, for thus the Lord will do to all your enemies
        against whom you fight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And afterward Joshua struck them and killed them, and hanged them
        on five trees; and they were hanging on the trees until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Conquest of the Southland'
      title: Conquest of the Southland
      number: 27
      content: "So it was at the time of the going down of the sun that Joshua commanded,
        and they took them down from the trees, cast them into the cave where they
        had been hidden, and laid large stones against the cave\u2019s mouth, which 
        remain until this very day."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "On that day Joshua took Makkedah, and struck it and its king with
        the edge of the sword. He utterly destroyed them\u2014all the people who
        were in it. He let none remain. He also did to the king of Makkedah as he
        had done to the king of Jericho."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Joshua passed from Makkedah, and all Israel with him, to Libnah;
        and they fought against Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And the Lord also delivered it and its king into the hand of Israel;
        he struck it and all the people who were in it with the edge of the sword.
        He let none remain in it, but did to its king as he had done to the king
        of Jericho.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Joshua passed from Libnah, and all Israel with him, to Lachish;
        and they encamped against it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the Lord delivered Lachish into the hand of Israel, who took
        it on the second day, and struck it and all the people who were in it with
        the edge of the sword, according to all that he had done to Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Then Horam king of Gezer came up to help Lachish; and Joshua struck
        him and his people, until he left him none remaining.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'From Lachish Joshua passed to Eglon, and all Israel with him; and
        they encamped against it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: They took it on that day and struck it with the edge of the sword;
        all the people who were in it he utterly destroyed that day, according to
        all that he had done to Lachish.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So Joshua went up from Eglon, and all Israel with him, to Hebron;
        and they fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And they took it and struck it with the edge of the sword\u2014its
        king, all its cities, and all the people who were in it; he left none remaining,
        according to all that he had done to Eglon, but utterly destroyed it and
        all the people who were in it."
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to Debir; and they
        fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: And he took it and its king and all its cities; they struck them with
        the edge of the sword and utterly destroyed all the people who were in it.
        He left none remaining; as he had done to Hebron, so he did to Debir and
        its king, as he had done also to Libnah and its king.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So Joshua conquered all the land: the mountain country and the South
        and the lowland and the wilderness slopes, and all their kings; he left none
        remaining, but utterly destroyed all that breathed, as the Lord God of Israel
        had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Joshua conquered them from Kadesh Barnea as far as Gaza, and
        all the country of Goshen, even as far as Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'All these kings and their land Joshua took at one time, because the
        Lord God of Israel fought for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Northern Conquest'
      title: The Northern Conquest
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Jabin king of Hazor heard these  things,
        that he sent to Jobab king of Madon, to the king of Shimron, to the king
        of Achshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and to the kings who were from the north, in the mountains, in the
        plain south of Chinneroth, in the lowland, and in the heights of Dor on the
        west, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'to the Canaanites in the east and in the west, the Amorite, the Hittite,
        the Perizzite, the Jebusite in the mountains, and the Hivite below Hermon
        in the land of Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they went out, they and all their armies with them, as many people
        as the sand that is on the seashore in multitude, with very many horses and
        chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And when all these kings had met together, they came and camped together
        at the waters of Merom to fight against Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CDo not be afraid because of them,
        for tomorrow about this time I will deliver all of them slain before Israel.
        You shall hamstring their horses and burn their chariots with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua and all the people of war with him came against them suddenly
        by the waters of Merom, and they attacked them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Lord delivered them into the hand of Israel, who defeated
        them and chased them to Greater Sidon, to the Brook Misrephoth, and to the
        Valley of Mizpah eastward; they attacked them until they left none of them
        remaining. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Joshua did to them as the Lord had told him: he hamstrung their
        horses and burned their chariots with fire.'
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Joshua turned back at that time and took Hazor, and struck its king
        with the sword; for Hazor was formerly the head of all those kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And they struck all the people who were in it with the edge of the
        sword, utterly destroying them. There was none left breathing. Then he burned
        Hazor with fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So all the cities of those kings, and all their kings, Joshua took
        and struck with the edge of the sword. He utterly destroyed them, as Moses
        the servant of the Lord had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But as  for the cities that stood on their mounds, Israel burned
        none of them, except Hazor only, which Joshua burned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the spoil of these cities and the livestock, the children
        of Israel took as booty for themselves; but they struck every man with the
        edge of the sword until they had destroyed them, and they left none breathing. '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Summary of Joshua\u2019s Conquests"
      title: "Summary of Joshua\u2019s Conquests"
      number: 15
      content: As the Lord had commanded Moses his servant, so Moses commanded Joshua,
        and so Joshua did. He left nothing undone of all that the Lord had commanded
        Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus Joshua took all this land: the mountain country, all the South,
        all the land of Goshen, the lowland, and the Jordan plain\u2014the mountains
        of Israel and its lowlands, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'from Mount Halak and the ascent to Seir, even as far as Baal Gad
        in the Valley of Lebanon below Mount Hermon. He captured all their kings,
        and struck them down and killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Joshua made war a long time with all those kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'There was not a city that made peace with the children of Israel,
        except the Hivites, the inhabitants of Gibeon. All the  others they took
        in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For it was of the Lord to harden their hearts, that they should come
        against Israel in battle, that He might utterly destroy them, and that they
        might receive no mercy, but that He might destroy them, as the Lord had commanded
        Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And at that time Joshua came and cut off the Anakim from the mountains:
        from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab, from all the mountains of Judah, and
        from all the mountains of Israel; Joshua utterly destroyed them with their
        cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: None of the Anakim were left in the land of the children of Israel;
        they remained only in Gaza, in Gath, and in Ashdod.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So Joshua took the whole land, according to all that the Lord had
        said to Moses; and Joshua gave it as an inheritance to Israel according to
        their divisions by their tribes. Then the land rested from war.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Kings Conquered by Moses'
      title: The Kings Conquered by Moses
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the kings of the land whom the children of Israel defeated,
        and whose land they possessed on the other side of the Jordan toward the
        rising of the sun, from the River Arnon to Mount Hermon, and all the eastern
        Jordan plain: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'One  king  was  Sihon king of the Amorites, who dwelt in Heshbon
        and ruled half of Gilead, from Aroer, which is on the bank of the River Arnon,
        from the middle of that river, even as far as the River Jabbok, which  is
        the border of the Ammonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the eastern Jordan plain from the Sea of Chinneroth as far as
        the Sea of the Arabah (the Salt Sea), the road to Beth Jeshimoth, and southward
        below the slopes of Pisgah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The  other  king  was  Og king of Bashan and his territory, who 
        was of the remnant of the giants, who dwelt at Ashtaroth and at Edrei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: and reigned over Mount Hermon, over Salcah, over all Bashan, as far
        as the border of the Geshurites and the Maachathites, and over half of Gilead
        to the border of Sihon king of Heshbon.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Kings Conquered by Joshua'
      title: The Kings Conquered by Joshua
      number: 6
      content: These Moses the servant of the Lord and the children of Israel had
        conquered; and Moses the servant of the Lord had given it as a possession
        to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And these are the kings of the country which Joshua and the children
        of Israel conquered on this side of the Jordan, on the west, from Baal Gad
        in the Valley of Lebanon as far as Mount Halak and the ascent to Seir, which
        Joshua gave to the tribes of Israel as a possession according to their divisions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "in the mountain country, in the lowlands, in the Jordan plain, in
        the slopes, in the wilderness, and in the South\u2014the Hittites, the Amorites,
        the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites: "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the king of Jericho, one; the king of Ai, which is beside Bethel,
        one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the king of Jerusalem, one; the king of Hebron, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the king of Jarmuth, one; the king of Lachish, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the king of Eglon, one; the king of Gezer, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the king of Debir, one; the king of Geder, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the king of Libnah, one; the king of Adullam, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the king of Makkedah, one; the king of Bethel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the king of Madon, one; the king of Hazor, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the king of Shimron Meron, one; the king of Achshaph, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the king of Taanach, one; the king of Megiddo, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam in Carmel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the king of Dor in the heights of Dor, one; the king of the people
        of Gilgal, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "the king of Tirzah, one\u2014all the kings, thirty-one."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Remaining Land to Be Conquered'
      title: Remaining Land to Be Conquered
      number: 1
      content: "Now Joshua was old, advanced in years. And the Lord said to him:
        \u201CYou are old, advanced in years, and there remains very much land yet
        to be possessed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This is the land that yet remains: all the territory of the Philistines
        and all that  of the Geshurites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "from Sihor, which is east of Egypt, as far as the border of Ekron
        northward (which is counted as Canaanite); the five lords of the Philistines\u2014the
        Gazites, the Ashdodites, the Ashkelonites, the Gittites, and the Ekronites;
        also the Avites; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'from the south, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that belongs
        to the Sidonians as far as Aphek, to the border of the Amorites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the land of the Gebalites, and all Lebanon, toward the sunrise, from
        Baal Gad below Mount Hermon as far as the entrance to Hamath; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "all the inhabitants of the mountains from Lebanon as far as the Brook
        Misrephoth, and all the Sidonians\u2014them I will drive out from before
        the children of Israel; only divide it by lot to Israel as an inheritance,
        as I have commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Land Divided East of the Jordan'
      title: The Land Divided East of the Jordan
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, divide this land as an inheritance to the nine tribes
        and half the tribe of Manasseh.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'With the other half-tribe the Reubenites and the Gadites received
        their inheritance, which Moses had given them, beyond the Jordan eastward,
        as Moses the servant of the Lord had given them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'from Aroer which is on the bank of the River Arnon, and the town
        that is in the midst of the ravine, and all the plain of Medeba as far as
        Dibon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon,
        as far as the border of the children of Ammon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Gilead, and the border of the Geshurites and Maachathites, all Mount
        Hermon, and all Bashan as far as Salcah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and Edrei,
        who remained of the remnant of the giants; for Moses had defeated and cast
        out these.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Nevertheless the children of Israel did not drive out the Geshurites
        or the Maachathites, but the Geshurites and the Maachathites dwell among
        the Israelites until this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Land of Reuben'
      title: The Land of Reuben
      number: 14
      content: Only to the tribe of Levi he had given no inheritance; the sacrifices
        of the Lord God of Israel made by fire are their inheritance, as He said
        to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Moses had given to the tribe of the children of Reuben an  inheritance
        according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their territory was from Aroer, which is on the bank of the River
        Arnon, and the city that is in the midst of the ravine, and all the plain
        by Medeba; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Heshbon and all its cities that are in the plain: Dibon, Bamoth Baal,
        Beth Baal Meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jahaza, Kedemoth, Mephaath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Kirjathaim, Sibmah, Zereth Shahar on the mountain of the valley, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Beth Peor, the slopes of Pisgah, and Beth Jeshimoth\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'all the cities of the plain and all the kingdom of Sihon king of
        the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, whom Moses had struck with the princes
        of Midian: Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba, who were princes of Sihon dwelling
        in the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The children of Israel also killed with the sword Balaam the son
        of Beor, the soothsayer, among those who were killed by them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Land of Gad'
      title: The Land of Gad
      number: 23
      content: And the border of the children of Reuben was the bank of the Jordan.
        This was the inheritance of the children of Reuben according to their families,
        the cities and their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moses also had given an  inheritance to the tribe of Gad, to the
        children of Gad according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their territory was Jazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and half
        the land of the Ammonites as far as Aroer, which is before Rabbah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and from Heshbon to Ramath Mizpah and Betonim, and from Mahanaim
        to the border of Debir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and in the valley Beth Haram, Beth Nimrah, Succoth, and Zaphon, the
        rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon, with the Jordan as its border,
        as far as the edge of the Sea of Chinnereth, on the other side of the Jordan
        eastward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Half the Tribe of Manasseh (East)'
      title: Half the Tribe of Manasseh (East)
      number: 28
      content: This is the inheritance of the children of Gad according to their
        families, the cities and their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Moses also had given an  inheritance to half the tribe of Manasseh;
        it was for half the tribe of the children of Manasseh according to their
        families: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Their territory was from Mahanaim, all Bashan, all the kingdom of
        Og king of Bashan, and all the towns of Jair which are in Bashan, sixty cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: half of Gilead, and Ashtaroth and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of
        Og in Bashan, were for the children of Machir the son of Manasseh, for half
        of the children of Machir according to their families.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'These are  the  areas which Moses had distributed as an inheritance
        in the plains of Moab on the other side of the Jordan, by Jericho eastward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: But to the tribe of Levi Moses had given no inheritance; the Lord
        God of Israel was their inheritance, as He had said to them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Land Divided West of the Jordan'
      title: The Land Divided West of the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: 'These are  the  areas which the children of Israel inherited in the
        land of Canaan, which Eleazar the priest, Joshua the son of Nun, and the
        heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel distributed
        as an inheritance to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their inheritance was  by lot, as the Lord had commanded by the hand
        of Moses, for the nine tribes and the half-tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Moses had given the inheritance of the two tribes and the half-tribe
        on the other side of the Jordan; but to the Levites he had given no inheritance
        among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the children of Joseph were two tribes: Manasseh and Ephraim.
        And they gave no part to the Levites in the land, except cities to dwell
        in, with their common-lands for their livestock and their property. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Caleb Inherits Hebron'
      title: Caleb Inherits Hebron
      number: 5
      content: As the Lord had commanded Moses, so the children of Israel did; and
        they divided the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the children of Judah came to Joshua in Gilgal. And Caleb the
        son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite said to him: \u201CYou know the word which
        the Lord said to Moses the man of God concerning you and me in Kadesh Barnea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the Lord  sent me
        from Kadesh Barnea to spy out the land, and I brought back word to him as
        it  was in my heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Nevertheless my brethren who went up with me made the heart of the
        people melt, but I wholly followed the Lord my God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Moses swore on that day, saying, \u2018Surely the land where your
        foot has trodden shall be your inheritance and your children\u2019s forever,
        because you have wholly followed the Lord my God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now, behold, the Lord has kept me alive, as He said, these forty-five
        years, ever since the Lord spoke this word to Moses while Israel wandered
        in the wilderness; and now, here I am this day, eighty-five years old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As yet I am  as strong this day as on the day that Moses sent me;
        just as my strength was then, so now is my strength for war, both for going
        out and for coming in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now therefore, give me this mountain of which the Lord spoke in that
        day; for you heard in that day how the Anakim were there, and that the cities
        were great and fortified. It may be that the Lord  will  be with me, and
        I shall be able to drive them out as the Lord said.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Joshua blessed him, and gave Hebron to Caleb the son of Jephunneh
        as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Hebron therefore became the inheritance of Caleb the son of Jephunneh
        the Kenizzite to this day, because he wholly followed the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And the name of Hebron formerly was Kirjath Arba (Arba  was the greatest
        man among the Anakim).Then the land had rest from war.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Land of Judah'
      title: The Land of Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'So this was the lot of the tribe of the children of Judah according
        to their families:The border of Edom at the Wilderness of Zin southward was
        the extreme southern boundary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And their southern border began at the shore of the Salt Sea, from
        the bay that faces southward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then it went out to the southern side of the Ascent of Akrabbim,
        passed along to Zin, ascended on the south side of Kadesh Barnea, passed
        along to Hezron, went up to Adar, and went around to Karkaa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: From  there it passed toward Azmon and went out to the Brook of Egypt;
        and the border ended at the sea. This shall be your southern border.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The east border was the Salt Sea as far as the mouth of the Jordan.And
        the border on the northern quarter began at the bay of the sea at the mouth
        of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The border went up to Beth Hoglah and passed north of Beth Arabah;
        and the border went up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the border went up toward Debir from the Valley of Achor, and
        it turned northward toward Gilgal, which is before the Ascent of Adummim,
        which is on the south side of the valley. The border continued toward the
        waters of En Shemesh and ended at En Rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the border went up by the Valley of the Son of Hinnom to the
        southern slope of the Jebusite city (which is Jerusalem). The border went
        up to the top of the mountain that lies before the Valley of Hinnom westward,
        which is at the end of the Valley of Rephaim northward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the border went around from the top of the hill to the fountain
        of the water of Nephtoah, and extended to the cities of Mount Ephron. And
        the border went around to Baalah (which is  Kirjath Jearim). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the border turned westward from Baalah to Mount Seir, passed
        along to the side of Mount Jearim on the north (which is Chesalon), went
        down to Beth Shemesh, and passed on to Timnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And the border went out to the side of Ekron northward. Then the border
        went around to Shicron, passed along to Mount Baalah, and extended to Jabneel;
        and the border ended at the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Caleb Occupies Hebron and Debir'
      title: Caleb Occupies Hebron and Debir
      number: 12
      content: The west border was  the coastline of the Great Sea. This is the boundary
        of the children of Judah all around according to their families.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now to Caleb the son of Jephunneh he gave a share among the children
        of Judah, according to the commandment of the Lord to Joshua, namely,  Kirjath
        Arba, which is Hebron (Arba  was the father of Anak). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Caleb drove out the three sons of Anak from there: Sheshai, Ahiman,
        and Talmai, the children of Anak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then he went up from there to the inhabitants of Debir (formerly the
        name of Debir was Kirjath Sepher).
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Caleb said, \u201CHe who attacks Kirjath Sepher and takes it,
        to him I will give Achsah my daughter as wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Othniel the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it; and he
        gave him Achsah his daughter as wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now it was so, when she came to  him, that she persuaded him to ask
        her father for a field. So she dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said
        to her, \u201CWhat do you wish?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Cities of Judah'
      title: The Cities of Judah
      number: 19
      content: "She answered, \u201CGive me a blessing; since you have given me land
        in the South, give me also springs of water.\u201D So he gave her the upper
        springs and the lower springs."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Judah according
        to their families:'
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The cities at the limits of the tribe of the children of Judah, toward
        the border of Edom in the South, were Kabzeel, Eder, Jagur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Ziph, Telem, Bealoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Hazor, Hadattah, Kerioth, Hezron (which is Hazor), '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Amam, Shema, Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hazar Gaddah, Heshmon, Beth Pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Hazar Shual, Beersheba, Bizjothjah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Baalah, Ijim, Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Eltolad, Chesil, Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon: all the cities are twenty-nine,
        with their villages.'
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the lowland: Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Zanoah, En Gannim, Tappuah, Enam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh, Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Sharaim, Adithaim, Gederah, and Gederothaim: fourteen cities with
        their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal Gad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Dilean, Mizpah, Joktheel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Lachish, Bozkath, Eglon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Cabbon, Lahmas, Kithlish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Gederoth, Beth Dagon, Naamah, and Makkedah: sixteen cities with their
        villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Libnah, Ether, Ashan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Jiphtah, Ashnah, Nezib, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Keilah, Achzib, and Mareshah: nine cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Ekron, with its towns and villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'from Ekron to the sea, all that lay near Ashdod, with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Ashdod with its towns and villages, Gaza with its towns and villages\u2014as
        far as the Brook of Egypt and the Great Sea with its coastline."
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And in the mountain country: Shamir, Jattir, Sochoh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Dannah, Kirjath Sannah (which is Debir), '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Goshen, Holon, and Giloh: eleven cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Arab, Dumah, Eshean, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Janum, Beth Tappuah, Aphekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Humtah, Kirjath Arba (which is Hebron), and Zior: nine cities with
        their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Maon, Carmel, Ziph, Juttah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Jezreel, Jokdeam, Zanoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah: ten cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Halhul, Beth Zur, Gedor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Maarath, Beth Anoth, and Eltekon: six cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'Kirjath Baal (which is Kirjath Jearim) and Rabbah: two cities with
        their villages.'
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'In the wilderness: Beth Arabah, Middin, Secacah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Nibshan, the City of Salt, and En Gedi: six cities with their villages.'
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: As for the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the children of
        Judah could not drive them out; but the Jebusites dwell with the children
        of Judah at Jerusalem to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ephraim and West Manasseh'
      title: Ephraim and West Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: 'The lot fell to the children of Joseph from the Jordan, by Jericho,
        to the waters of Jericho on the east, to the wilderness that goes up from
        Jericho through the mountains to Bethel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then went out from Bethel to Luz, passed along to the border of the
        Archites at Ataroth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: and went down westward to the boundary of the Japhletites, as far
        as the boundary of Lower Beth Horon to Gezer; and it ended at the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Land of Ephraim'
      title: The Land of Ephraim
      number: 4
      content: So the children of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, took their inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The border of the children of Ephraim, according to their families,
        was thus: The border of their inheritance on the east side was Ataroth Addar
        as far as Upper Beth Horon.'
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the border went out toward the sea on the north side of Michmethath;
        then the border went around eastward to Taanath Shiloh, and passed by it
        on the east of Janohah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then it went down from Janohah to Ataroth and Naarah, reached to Jericho,
        and came out at the Jordan.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The border went out from Tappuah westward to the Brook Kanah, and
        it ended at the sea. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children
        of Ephraim according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The separate cities for the children of Ephraim were among the inheritance
        of the children of Manasseh, all the cities with their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And they did not drive out the Canaanites who dwelt in Gezer; but
        the Canaanites dwell among the Ephraimites to this day and have become forced
        laborers.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Other Half-Tribe of Manasseh (West)'
      title: The Other Half-Tribe of Manasseh (West)
      number: 1
      content: 'There was also a lot for the tribe of Manasseh, for he was the firstborn
        of Joseph: namely for Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead,
        because he was a man of war; therefore he was given Gilead and Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And there was a  lot for the rest of the children of Manasseh according
        to their families: for the children of Abiezer, the children of Helek, the
        children of Asriel, the children of Shechem, the children of Hepher, and
        the children of Shemida; these were the male children of Manasseh the son
        of Joseph according to their families.'
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Zelophehad the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir,
        the son of Manasseh, had no sons, but only daughters. And these are the names
        of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they came near before Eleazar the priest, before Joshua the son
        of Nun, and before the rulers, saying, \u201CThe Lord commanded Moses to
        give us an inheritance among our brothers.\u201D Therefore, according to
        the commandment of the Lord, he gave them an inheritance among their father\u2019s
        brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ten shares fell to Manasseh, besides the land of Gilead and Bashan,
        which were on the other side of the Jordan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "because the daughters of Manasseh received an inheritance among his
        sons; and the rest of Manasseh\u2019s sons had the land of Gilead."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the territory of Manasseh was from Asher to Michmethath, that
        lies east of Shechem; and the border went along south to the inhabitants
        of En Tappuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Manasseh had the land of Tappuah, but Tappuah on the border of Manasseh
        belonged to the children of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And the border descended to the Brook Kanah, southward to the brook.
        These cities of Ephraim are among the cities of Manasseh. The border of Manasseh
        was on the north side of the brook; and it ended at the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Southward it  was Ephraim\u2019s, northward it  was Manasseh\u2019s,
        and the sea was its border. Manasseh\u2019s territory was adjoining Asher
        on the north and Issachar on the east. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And in Issachar and in Asher, Manasseh had Beth Shean and its towns,
        Ibleam and its towns, the inhabitants of Dor and its towns, the inhabitants
        of En Dor and its towns, the inhabitants of Taanach and its towns, and the
        inhabitants of Megiddo and its towns\u2014three hilly regions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yet the children of Manasseh could not drive out the  inhabitants 
        of those cities, but the Canaanites were determined to dwell in that land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: More Land for Ephraim and Manasseh'
      title: More Land for Ephraim and Manasseh
      number: 13
      content: And it happened, when the children of Israel grew strong, that they
        put the Canaanites to forced labor, but did not utterly drive them out.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the children of Joseph spoke to Joshua, saying, \u201CWhy have
        you given us only  one lot and one share to inherit, since we are  a great
        people, inasmuch as the Lord has blessed us until now?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Joshua answered them, \u201CIf you are a great people, then go
        up to the forest country and clear a place for yourself there in the land
        of the Perizzites and the giants, since the mountains of Ephraim are too
        confined for you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But the children of Joseph said, \u201CThe mountain country is not
        enough for us; and all the Canaanites who dwell in the land of the valley
        have chariots of iron, both  those who are of Beth Shean and its towns and
        those who are  of the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Joshua spoke to the house of Joseph\u2014to Ephraim and Manasseh\u2014saying,
        \u201CYou are a great people and have great power; you shall not have only
        one lot, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "but the mountain country shall be yours. Although it is wooded, you
        shall cut it down, and its farthest extent shall be yours; for you shall
        drive out the Canaanites, though they have iron chariots and are strong.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Remainder of the Land Divided'
      title: The Remainder of the Land Divided
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the whole congregation of the children of Israel assembled together
        at Shiloh, and set up the tabernacle of meeting there. And the land was subdued
        before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: But there remained among the children of Israel seven tribes which
        had not yet received their inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Joshua said to the children of Israel: \u201CHow long will you
        neglect to go and possess the land which the Lord God of your fathers has
        given you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Pick out from among you three men for each tribe, and I will send
        them; they shall rise and go through the land, survey it according to their
        inheritance, and come back to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they shall divide it into seven parts. Judah shall remain in
        their territory on the south, and the house of Joseph shall remain in their
        territory on the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall therefore survey the land in seven parts and bring the 
        survey here to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the Lord our
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the Levites have no part among you, for the priesthood of the
        Lord  is their inheritance. And Gad, Reuben, and half the tribe of Manasseh
        have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan on the east, which Moses
        the servant of the Lord gave them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the men arose to go away; and Joshua charged those who went
        to survey the land, saying, \u201CGo, walk through the land, survey it, and
        come back to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the Lord in Shiloh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the men went, passed through the land, and wrote the survey in
        a book in seven parts by cities; and they came to Joshua at the camp in Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Land of Benjamin'
      title: The Land of Benjamin
      number: 10
      content: Then Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the Lord, and there
        Joshua divided the land to the children of Israel according to their divisions.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the lot of the tribe of the children of Benjamin came up according
        to their families, and the territory of their lot came out between the children
        of Judah and the children of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Their border on the north side began at the Jordan, and the border
        went up to the side of Jericho on the north, and went up through the mountains
        westward; it ended at the Wilderness of Beth Aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The border went over from there toward Luz, to the side of Luz (which
        is Bethel) southward; and the border descended to Ataroth Addar, near the
        hill that lies on the south side of Lower Beth Horon.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then the border extended around the west side to the south, from the
        hill that lies before Beth Horon southward; and it ended at Kirjath Baal
        (which is Kirjath Jearim), a city of the children of Judah. This was the
        west side.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The south side began at the end of Kirjath Jearim, and the border
        extended on the west and went out to the spring of the waters of Nephtoah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the border came down to the end of the mountain that lies before
        the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, which is in the Valley of the Rephaim on
        the north, descended to the Valley of Hinnom, to the side of the Jebusite
        city on the south, and descended to En Rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it went around from the north, went out to En Shemesh, and extended
        toward Geliloth, which is before the Ascent of Adummim, and descended to
        the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then it passed along toward the north side of Arabah, and went down
        to Arabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And the border passed along to the north side of Beth Hoglah; then
        the border ended at the north bay at the Salt Sea, at the south end of the
        Jordan. This was the southern boundary.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The Jordan was its border on the east side. This was the inheritance
        of the children of Benjamin, according to its boundaries all around, according
        to their families.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the cities of the tribe of the children of Benjamin, according
        to their families, were Jericho, Beth Hoglah, Emek Keziz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Beth Arabah, Zemaraim, Bethel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Avim, Parah, Ophrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Chephar Haammoni, Ophni, and Gaba: twelve cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Gibeon, Ramah, Beeroth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Mizpah, Chephirah, Mozah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Rekem, Irpeel, Taralah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Zelah, Eleph, Jebus (which is Jerusalem), Gibeath, and Kirjath: fourteen
        cities with their villages. This was the inheritance of the children of Benjamin
        according to their families.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Simeon\u2019s Inheritance with Judah"
      title: "Simeon\u2019s Inheritance with Judah"
      number: 1
      content: 'The second lot came out for Simeon, for the tribe of the children
        of Simeon according to their families. And their inheritance was within the
        inheritance of the children of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They had in their inheritance Beersheba (Sheba), Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Hazar Shual, Balah, Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ziklag, Beth Marcaboth, Hazar Susah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Beth Lebaoth, and Sharuhen: thirteen cities and their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan: four cities and their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: and all the villages that were all around these cities as far as Baalath
        Beer, Ramah of the South. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children
        of Simeon according to their families.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Land of Zebulun'
      title: The Land of Zebulun
      number: 9
      content: The inheritance of the children of Simeon was  included in the share
        of the children of Judah, for the share of the children of Judah was too
        much for them. Therefore the children of Simeon had their inheritance within
        the inheritance of that people.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The third lot came out for the children of Zebulun according to their
        families, and the border of their inheritance was as far as Sarid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Their border went toward the west and to Maralah, went to Dabbasheth,
        and extended along the brook that is east of Jokneam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then from Sarid it went eastward toward the sunrise along the border
        of Chisloth Tabor, and went out toward Daberath, bypassing Japhia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And from there it passed along on the east of Gath Hepher, toward
        Eth Kazin, and extended to Rimmon, which borders on Neah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the border went around it on the north side of Hannathon, and
        it ended in the Valley of Jiphthah El. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Included were Kattath, Nahallal, Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem:
        twelve cities with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Land of Issachar'
      title: The Land of Issachar
      number: 16
      content: This was the inheritance of the children of Zebulun according to their
        families, these cities with their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The fourth lot came out to Issachar, for the children of Issachar
        according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And their territory went to Jezreel, and included Chesulloth, Shunem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Haphraim, Shion, Anaharath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Rabbith, Kishion, Abez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Remeth, En Gannim, En Haddah, and Beth Pazzez. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the border reached to Tabor, Shahazimah, and Beth Shemesh; their
        border ended at the Jordan: sixteen cities with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Land of Asher'
      title: The Land of Asher
      number: 23
      content: This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Issachar
        according to their families, the cities and their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The fifth lot came out for the tribe of the children of Asher according
        to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And their territory included Helkath, Hali, Beten, Achshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Alammelech, Amad, and Mishal; it reached to Mount Carmel westward,
        along the  Brook Shihor Libnath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'It turned toward the sunrise to Beth Dagon; and it reached to Zebulun
        and to the Valley of Jiphthah El, then northward beyond Beth Emek and Neiel,
        bypassing Cabul which  was on the left, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'including Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, and Kanah, as far as Greater Sidon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the border turned to Ramah and to the fortified city of Tyre;
        then the border turned to Hosah, and ended at the sea by the region of Achzib. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Also Ummah, Aphek, and Rehob were  included: twenty-two cities with
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Land of Naphtali'
      title: The Land of Naphtali
      number: 31
      content: This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Asher according
        to their families, these cities with their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The sixth lot came out to the children of Naphtali, for the children
        of Naphtali according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And their border began at Heleph, enclosing the territory from the
        terebinth tree in Zaanannim, Adami Nekeb, and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum;
        it ended at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'From Heleph the border extended westward to Aznoth Tabor, and went
        out from there toward Hukkok; it adjoined Zebulun on the south side and Asher
        on the west side, and ended at Judah by the Jordan toward the sunrise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, Chinnereth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Adamah, Ramah, Hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Kedesh, Edrei, En Hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Iron, Migdal El, Horem, Beth Anath, and Beth Shemesh: nineteen cities
        with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: The Land of Dan'
      title: The Land of Dan
      number: 39
      content: This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Naphtali
        according to their families, the cities and their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The seventh lot came out for the tribe of the children of Dan according
        to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the territory of their inheritance was Zorah, Eshtaol, Ir Shemesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Shaalabbin, Aijalon, Jethlah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Elon, Timnah, Ekron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jehud, Bene Berak, Gath Rimmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Me Jarkon, and Rakkon, with the region near Joppa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And the border of the children of Dan went beyond these, because
        the children of Dan went up to fight against Leshem and took it; and they
        struck it with the edge of the sword, took possession of it, and dwelt in
        it. They called Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: "48: Joshua\u2019s Inheritance"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Inheritance"
      number: 48
      content: This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Dan according
        to their families, these cities with their villages.
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'When they had made an end of dividing the land as an inheritance
        according to their borders, the children of Israel gave an inheritance among
        them to Joshua the son of Nun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: According to the word of the Lord they gave him the city which he
        asked for, Timnath Serah in the mountains of Ephraim; and he built the city
        and dwelt in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: These were the inheritances which Eleazar the priest, Joshua the son
        of Nun, and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel
        divided as an inheritance by lot in Shiloh before the Lord, at the door of
        the tabernacle of meeting. So they made an end of dividing the country.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Cities of Refuge'
      title: The Cities of Refuge
      number: 1
      content: 'The Lord also spoke to Joshua, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak to the children of Israel, saying: \u2018Appoint for
        yourselves cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through Moses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that the slayer who kills a person accidentally or unintentionally
        may flee there; and they shall be your refuge from the avenger of blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when he flees to one of those cities, and stands at the entrance
        of the gate of the city, and declares his case in the hearing of the elders
        of that city, they shall take him into the city as one of them, and give
        him a place, that he may dwell among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then if the avenger of blood pursues him, they shall not deliver
        the slayer into his hand, because he struck his neighbor unintentionally,
        but did not hate him beforehand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he shall dwell in that city until he stands before the congregation
        for judgment, and until the death of the one who is high priest in those
        days. Then the slayer may return and come to his own city and his own house,
        to the city from which he fled.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they appointed Kedesh in Galilee, in the mountains of Naphtali,
        Shechem in the mountains of Ephraim, and Kirjath Arba (which is Hebron) in
        the mountains of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And on the other side of the Jordan, by Jericho eastward, they assigned
        Bezer in the wilderness on the plain, from the tribe of Reuben, Ramoth in
        Gilead, from the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan, from the tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: These were the cities appointed for all the children of Israel and
        for the stranger who dwelt among them, that whoever killed a person accidentally
        might flee there, and not die by the hand of the avenger of blood until he
        stood before the congregation.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cities of the Levites'
      title: Cities of the Levites
      number: 1
      content: "Then the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of the Levites came near
        to Eleazar the priest, to Joshua the son of Nun, and to the heads of the
        fathers\u2019 houses of the tribes of the children of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And they spoke to them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, saying, \u201CThe
        Lord commanded through Moses to give us cities to dwell in, with their common-lands
        for our livestock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the children of Israel gave to the Levites from their inheritance,
        at the commandment of the Lord, these cities and their common-lands:'
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the lot came out for the families of the Kohathites. And the
        children of Aaron the priest, who  were of the Levites, had thirteen cities
        by lot from the tribe of Judah, from the tribe of Simeon, and from the tribe
        of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The rest of the children of Kohath had ten cities by lot from the
        families of the tribe of Ephraim, from the tribe of Dan, and from the half-tribe
        of Manasseh.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And the children of Gershon had thirteen cities by lot from the families
        of the tribe of Issachar, from the tribe of Asher, from the tribe of Naphtali,
        and from the half-tribe of Manasseh in Bashan.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The children of Merari according to their families had twelve cities
        from the tribe of Reuben, from the tribe of Gad, and from the tribe of Zebulun.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And the children of Israel gave these cities with their common-lands
        by lot to the Levites, as the Lord had commanded by the hand of Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So they gave from the tribe of the children of Judah and from the
        tribe of the children of Simeon these cities which are designated by name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'which were for the children of Aaron, one of the families of the
        Kohathites, who  were of the children of Levi; for the lot was theirs first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they gave them Kirjath Arba (Arba  was the father of Anak), which
        is Hebron, in the mountains of Judah, with the common-land surrounding it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But the fields of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb the
        son of Jephunneh as his possession.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Thus to the children of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron with its
        common-land (a city of refuge for the slayer), Libnah with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jattir with its common-land, Eshtemoa with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Holon with its common-land, Debir with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ain with its common-land, Juttah with its common-land, and Beth Shemesh
        with its common-land: nine cities from those two tribes; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and from the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon with its common-land, Geba
        with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Anathoth with its common-land, and Almon with its common-land: four
        cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: All the cities of the children of Aaron, the priests, were thirteen
        cities with their common-lands.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the families of the children of Kohath, the Levites, the rest
        of the children of Kohath, even they had the cities of their lot from the
        tribe of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For they gave them Shechem with its common-land in the mountains
        of Ephraim (a city of refuge for the slayer), Gezer with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Kibzaim with its common-land, and Beth Horon with its common-land:
        four cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and from the tribe of Dan, Eltekeh with its common-land, Gibbethon
        with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Aijalon with its common-land, and Gath Rimmon with its common-land:
        four cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and from the half-tribe of Manasseh, Tanach with its common-land
        and Gath Rimmon with its common-land: two cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: All the ten cities with their common-lands were for the rest of the
        families of the children of Kohath.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Also to the children of Gershon, of the families of the Levites,
        from the other half-tribe of Manasseh, they  gave  Golan in Bashan with its
        common-land (a city of refuge for the slayer), and Be Eshterah with its common-land:
        two cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and from the tribe of Issachar, Kishion with its common-land, Daberath
        with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Jarmuth with its common-land, and En Gannim with its common-land:
        four cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and from the tribe of Asher, Mishal with its common-land, Abdon with
        its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Helkath with its common-land, and Rehob with its common-land: four
        cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and from the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with its common-land
        (a city of refuge for the slayer), Hammoth Dor with its common-land, and
        Kartan with its common-land: three cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: All the cities of the Gershonites according to their families were
        thirteen cities with their common-lands.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And to the families of the children of Merari, the rest of the Levites,
        from the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with its common-land, Kartah with its
        common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Dimnah with its common-land, and Nahalal with its common-land: four
        cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and from the tribe of Reuben, Bezer with its common-land, Jahaz with
        its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Kedemoth with its common-land, and Mephaath with its common-land:
        four cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and from the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with its common-land
        (a city of refuge for the slayer), Mahanaim with its common-land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Heshbon with its common-land, and Jazer with its common-land: four
        cities in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: So all the cities for the children of Merari according to their families,
        the rest of the families of the Levites, were by their lot twelve cities.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'All the cities of the Levites within the possession of the children
        of Israel were forty-eight cities with their common-lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: The Promise Fulfilled'
      title: The Promise Fulfilled
      number: 42
      content: Every one of these cities had its common-land surrounding it; thus
        were all these cities.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So the Lord gave to Israel all the land of which He had sworn to
        give to their fathers, and they took possession of it and dwelt in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The Lord gave them rest all around, according to all that He had
        sworn to their fathers. And not a man of all their enemies stood against
        them; the Lord delivered all their enemies into their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: Not a word failed of any good thing which the Lord had spoken to the
        house of Israel. All came to pass.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eastern Tribes Return to Their Lands'
      title: Eastern Tribes Return to Their Lands
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Joshua called the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe
        of Manasseh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to them: \u201CYou have kept all that Moses the servant
        of the Lord commanded you, and have obeyed my voice in all that I commanded
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have not left your brethren these many days, up to this day,
        but have kept the charge of the commandment of the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And now the Lord your God has given rest to your brethren, as He
        promised them; now therefore, return and go to your tents and to the land
        of your possession, which Moses the servant of the Lord gave you on the other
        side of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But take careful heed to do the commandment and the law which Moses
        the servant of the Lord commanded you, to love the Lord your God, to walk
        in all His ways, to keep His commandments, to hold fast to Him, and to serve
        Him with all your heart and with all your soul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So Joshua blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their
        tents.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now to half the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession in
        Bashan, but to the other half of it Joshua gave a  possession among their
        brethren on this side of the Jordan, westward. And indeed, when Joshua sent
        them away to their tents, he blessed them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and spoke to them, saying, \u201CReturn with much riches to your
        tents, with very much livestock, with silver, with gold, with bronze, with
        iron, and with very much clothing. Divide the spoil of your enemies with
        your brethren.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: An Altar by the Jordan'
      title: An Altar by the Jordan
      number: 9
      content: So the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe
        of Manasseh returned, and departed from the children of Israel at Shiloh,
        which is in the land of Canaan, to go to the country of Gilead, to the land
        of their possession, which they had obtained according to the word of the
        Lord by the hand of Moses.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And when they came to the region of the Jordan which is in the land
        of Canaan, the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe
        of Manasseh built an altar there by the Jordan\u2014a great, impressive altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now the children of Israel heard someone say, \u201CBehold, the children
        of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh have built
        an altar on the frontier of the land of Canaan, in the region of the Jordan\u2014on
        the children of Israel\u2019s side.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And when the children of Israel heard of  it,  the whole congregation
        of the children of Israel gathered together at Shiloh to go to war against
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the children of Israel sent Phinehas the son of Eleazar the
        priest to the children of Reuben, to the children of Gad, and to half the
        tribe of Manasseh, into the land of Gilead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and with him ten rulers, one ruler each from the chief house of every
        tribe of Israel; and each one was the head of the house of his father among
        the divisions of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then they came to the children of Reuben, to the children of Gad,
        and to half the tribe of Manasseh, to the land of Gilead, and they spoke
        with them, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThus says the whole congregation of the Lord: \u2018What treachery
        is this that you have committed against the God of Israel, to turn away this
        day from following the Lord, in that you have built for yourselves an altar,
        that you might rebel this day against the Lord? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Is the iniquity of Peor not enough for us, from which we are not
        cleansed till this day, although there was a plague in the congregation of
        the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'but that you must turn away this day from following the Lord? And
        it shall be, if you rebel today against the Lord, that tomorrow He will be
        angry with the whole congregation of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Nevertheless, if the land of your possession is unclean, then cross
        over to the land of the possession of the Lord, where the Lord\u2019s tabernacle
        stands, and take possession among us; but do not rebel against the Lord,
        nor rebel against us, by building yourselves an altar besides the altar of
        the Lord our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Did not Achan the son of Zerah commit a trespass in the accursed
        thing, and wrath fell on all the congregation of Israel? And that man did
        not perish alone in his iniquity.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe
        of Manasseh answered and said to the heads of the divisions of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe Lord  God of gods, the Lord God of gods, He knows, and
        let Israel itself know\u2014if it  is in rebellion, or if in treachery against
        the Lord, do not save us this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If we have built ourselves an altar to turn from following the Lord,
        or if to offer on it burnt offerings or grain offerings, or if to offer peace
        offerings on it, let the Lord Himself require an  account.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But in fact we have done it for fear, for a reason, saying, \u2018In
        time to come your descendants may speak to our descendants, saying, \u201CWhat
        have you to do with the Lord God of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For the Lord has made the Jordan a border between you and us, you
        children of Reuben and children of Gad. You have no part in the Lord.\u201D
        So your descendants would make our descendants cease fearing the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore we said, \u2018Let us now prepare to build ourselves an
        altar, not for burnt offering nor for sacrifice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "but that it may  be  a witness between you and us and our generations
        after us, that we may perform the service of the Lord before Him with our
        burnt offerings, with our sacrifices, and with our peace offerings; that
        your descendants may not say to our descendants in time to come, \u201CYou
        have no part in the Lord.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore we said that it will be, when they say this to us or to
        our generations in time to come, that we may say, \u2018Here is the replica
        of the altar of the Lord which our fathers made, though not for burnt offerings
        nor for sacrifices; but it is a witness between you and us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Far be it from us that we should rebel against the Lord, and turn
        from following the Lord this day, to build an altar for burnt offerings,
        for grain offerings, or for sacrifices, besides the altar of the Lord our
        God which is before His tabernacle.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now when Phinehas the priest and the rulers of the congregation,
        the heads of the divisions of Israel who were with him, heard the words that
        the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and the children of Manasseh
        spoke, it pleased them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest said to the children
        of Reuben, the children of Gad, and the children of Manasseh, \u201CThis
        day we perceive that the Lord  is  among us, because you have not committed
        this treachery against the Lord. Now you have delivered the children of Israel
        out of the hand of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, and the rulers, returned
        from the children of Reuben and the children of Gad, from the land of Gilead
        to the land of Canaan, to the children of Israel, and brought back word to
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So the thing pleased the children of Israel, and the children of Israel
        blessed God; they spoke no more of going against them in battle, to destroy
        the land where the children of Reuben and Gad dwelt.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The children of Reuben and the children of Gad called the altar,
        Witness, \u201CFor it  is a witness between us that the Lord  is God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joshua\u2019s Farewell Address"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Farewell Address"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass, a long time after the Lord  had given rest to
        Israel from all their enemies round about, that Joshua was old, advanced
        in age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Joshua called for all Israel, for their elders, for their heads,
        for their judges, and for their officers, and said to them:\u201CI am old,
        advanced in age. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have seen all that the Lord your God has done to all these nations
        because of you, for the Lord your God is He who has fought for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'See, I have divided to you by lot these nations that remain, to be
        an inheritance for your tribes, from the Jordan, with all the nations that
        I have cut off, as far as the Great Sea westward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the Lord your God will expel them from before you and drive them
        out of your sight. So you shall possess their land, as the Lord your God
        promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore be very courageous to keep and to do all that is written
        in the Book of the Law of Moses, lest you turn aside from it to the right
        hand or to the left, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and lest you go among these nations, these who remain among you.
        You shall not make mention of the name of their gods, nor cause anyone to
        swear by  them; you shall not serve them nor bow down to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but you shall hold fast to the Lord your God, as you have done to
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the Lord has driven out from before you great and strong nations;
        but as  for you, no one has been able to stand against you to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'One man of you shall chase a thousand, for the Lord your God is He
        who fights for you, as He promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore take careful heed to yourselves, that you love the Lord
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Or else, if indeed you do go back, and cling to the remnant of these
        nations\u2014these that remain among you\u2014and make marriages with them,
        and go in to them and they to you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: know for certain that the Lord your God will no longer drive out these
        nations from before you. But they shall be snares and traps to you, and scourges
        on your sides and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from this good land
        which the Lord your God has given you.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBehold, this day I am going the way of all the earth. And you
        know in all your hearts and in all your souls that not one thing has failed
        of all the good things which the Lord your God spoke concerning you. All
        have come to pass for you; not one word of them has failed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore it shall come to pass, that as all the good things have
        come upon you which the Lord your God promised you, so the Lord will bring
        upon you all harmful things, until He has destroyed you from this good land
        which the Lord your God has given you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When you have transgressed the covenant of the Lord your God, which
        He commanded you, and have gone and served other gods, and bowed down to
        them, then the anger of the Lord will burn against you, and you shall perish
        quickly from the good land which He has given you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Covenant at Shechem'
      title: The Covenant at Shechem
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem and called
        for the elders of Israel, for their heads, for their judges, and for their
        officers; and they presented themselves before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Joshua said to all the people, \u201CThus says the Lord God of
        Israel: \u2018Your fathers, including Terah, the father of Abraham and the
        father of Nahor, dwelt on the other side of the River in old times; and they
        served other gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I took your father Abraham from the other side of the River,
        led him throughout all the land of Canaan, and multiplied his descendants
        and gave him Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'To Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau. To Esau I gave the mountains of Seir
        to possess, but Jacob and his children went down to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Also I sent Moses and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt, according to what
        I did among them. Afterward I brought you out.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Then I brought your fathers out of Egypt, and you came to the
        sea; and the Egyptians pursued your fathers with chariots and horsemen to
        the Red Sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they cried out to the Lord; and He put darkness between you and
        the Egyptians, brought the sea upon them, and covered them. And your eyes
        saw what I did in Egypt. Then you dwelt in the wilderness a long time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I brought you into the land of the Amorites, who dwelt on the
        other side of the Jordan, and they fought with you. But I gave them into
        your hand, that you might possess their land, and I destroyed them from before
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, arose to make war against
        Israel, and sent and called Balaam the son of Beor to curse you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But I would not listen to Balaam; therefore he continued to bless
        you. So I delivered you out of his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then you went over the Jordan and came to Jericho. And the men of
        Jericho fought against you\u2014also the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites,
        the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites. But I delivered
        them into your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I sent the hornet before you which drove them out from before you,
        also the two kings of the Amorites, but  not with your sword or with your
        bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I have given you a land for which you did not labor, and cities which
        you did not build, and you dwell in them; you eat of the vineyards and olive
        groves which you did not plant.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, fear the Lord, serve Him in sincerity and in
        truth, and put away the gods which your fathers served on the other side
        of the River and in Egypt. Serve the Lord! "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And if it seems evil to you to serve the Lord, choose for yourselves
        this day whom you will serve, whether the gods which your fathers served
        that were on the other side of the River, or the gods of the Amorites, in
        whose land you dwell. But as for me and my house, we will serve the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So the people answered and said: \u201CFar be it from us that we
        should forsake the Lord to serve other gods; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for the Lord our God is He who brought us and our fathers up out
        of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage, who did those great signs
        in our sight, and preserved us in all the way that we went and among all
        the people through whom we passed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the Lord drove out from before us all the people, including the
        Amorites who dwelt in the land. We also will serve the Lord, for He is our
        God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou cannot serve the Lord, for
        He is a holy God. He is  a jealous God; He will not forgive your transgressions
        nor your sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "If you forsake the Lord and serve foreign gods, then He will turn
        and do you harm and consume you, after He has done you good.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the people said to Joshua, \u201CNo, but we will serve the Lord!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou are witnesses against yourselves
        that you have chosen the Lord for yourselves, to serve Him.\u201DAnd they
        said, \u201CWe  are witnesses!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CNow therefore,\u201D he  said,  \u201Cput away the foreign
        gods which are among you, and incline your heart to the Lord God of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the people said to Joshua, \u201CThe Lord our God we will serve,
        and His voice we will obey!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day, and made for them
        a statute and an ordinance in Shechem.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Joshua wrote these words in the Book of the Law of God. And
        he took a large stone, and set it up there under the oak that was by the
        sanctuary of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joshua said to all the people, \u201CBehold, this stone shall
        be a witness to us, for it has heard all the words of the Lord which He spoke
        to us. It shall therefore be a witness to you, lest you deny your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Death of Joshua and Eleazar'
      title: Death of Joshua and Eleazar
      number: 28
      content: So Joshua let the people depart, each to his own inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now it came to pass after these things that Joshua the son of Nun,
        the servant of the Lord, died, being one hundred and ten years old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And they buried him within the border of his inheritance at Timnath
        Serah, which is in the mountains of Ephraim, on the north side of Mount Gaash.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Israel served the Lord all the days of Joshua, and all the days of
        the elders who outlived Joshua, who had known all the works of the Lord which
        He had done for Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The bones of Joseph, which the children of Israel had brought up out
        of Egypt, they buried at Shechem, in the plot of ground which Jacob had bought
        from the sons of Hamor the father of Shechem for one hundred pieces of silver,
        and which had become an inheritance of the children of Joseph.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And Eleazar the son of Aaron died. They buried him in a hill belonging 
        to  Phinehas his son, which was given to him in the mountains of Ephraim.
      comments: []
